This is definitely a grower
this is perfection. for so many reasons. Pharell was both the best of and the worst of sweetener so I've just been waiting for him to come back through with another banger pop production. And it made me realize this is how it should be - when a producer is as integral to the song as the performer, we should have them credited. Obviously this happens already esp in the edm genre but it's high time that with as much access to information as we have, we recognize that performers are not the end all, be all of an artistic creation. this puts less pressure on them via the madness that is "celebrity" (think Doja, Britney, Gaga, so many others), and shifts the attention to other collaborators.   I hope this makes sense (: I know it seems silly to care so much about "the future of pop" but it is so deeply integral to our collective consciousness whether we notice it or not. so ofc I'm always so delighted when talent like this hits trending, it shows how versatile and powerful pop is ğŸ¥°

The buccal fat surgery is great when you're 30 and want fat removed however that very fat that you girls are all removing to do for you what blusher and highlighter can do sans surgery,is going to cause every one to age more quickly. That's exactly what aging is the loss of all the fat and collagen and estrogen and JUICY STUFF that plumps us up. So they are ALL going to have to have that fat replaced and one might say SO WHAT! I WILL JUST REPLACE IT! that's not the real ğŸŒ tho because EVERY TIME THE BODY IS INVADED WHETHER WITH OUR OWN FAT OR FILLER IT DOES NOT MATTER WHICH ONE EITHER THERE ARE SCARS. THERE IS SCARRING ANY TIME THE BODY IS INVADED BY anything So you aren't simply adding and taking away like a glass of water. You are adding and taking away materials that have to BIND TO THE EXISTING MATERIEALS IE. YOUR FACE AND BODY and there are internal scars created when no incisions are ever even used. Those fats and fillers HAVE TO BIND to the existing tissues and when that binding happens scarring also happens. Internal scarring can be Much WORSE than exterior scarring. When you are looking at a person whose had blephiraplasties and EVERYONE is la has had them if they are 25 or older,you will see linear scarring UNDER their facial skin almost always. It's ALL got consequences. There is no such thing as a consequence free successful procedure when you start augmenting the face in particular. I've gone off on a tangent Abt linear scarring! Lmfao!
